    "# Homework 5 (line detection/rectangle detection\n",
    "\n",
    "Student: Stanca Robert-Gabriel - ISI\n",
    "\n",
    "A: Choose five images containing lines and rectangular structures,\n",
    "from images.google.com. Examples of such images are those from\n",
    "urban scenes, buildings facades, repeated patterns (fences, trees,\n",
    "regular textures). The idea is that these images should contain a\n",
    "sufficient number of line segments ( > 30)\n",
    "\n",
    "B: Design and Implement an algorithm for automatic detection of\n",
    "lines (using for example RANSAC with Least Squares fitting, or the\n",
    "Hough Transform – be creative and try to develop a method that\n",
    "works well. Design it and implement it yourself! ☺\n",
    "\n",
    "C: Design and Implement a method for automatic detection of\n",
    "rectangular structures, using the output from B. Examples of such\n",
    "structures could be windows, houses, parts of cars or buildings –\n",
    "many man-made structures contain rectangular subparts"
   ]

    "# Hough Transform"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def clip(idx):\n",
    "    return int(max(idx,0))\n",
    "\n",
    "def hough_peaks(H, nps=1, e=100, size=5):\n",
    "    p = np.zeros((nps,2), dtype=np.uint64)\n",
    "    temp_H = H.copy()\n",
    "    for i in range(nps):\n",
    "        _,max_val,_,max_loc = cv2.minMaxLoc(temp_H) \n",
    "        if max_val > e:\n",
    "            p[i] = max_loc\n",
    "            (c,r) = max_loc\n",
    "            t = size//2.0\n",
    "            temp_H[clip(r-t):int(r+t+1), clip(c-t):int(c+t+1)] = 0\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            p = p[:i]\n",
    "            break\n",
    "    return p[:,::-1]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def hough_lines(img, rho_res=1, thetas=np.arange(-90,90,1)):\n",
    "    rho_max = int(np.linalg.norm(img.shape-np.array([1,1]), 2));\n",
    "    rhos = np.arange(-rho_max, rho_max, rho_res)\n",
    "    thetas -= min(min(thetas),0)\n",
    "    accumulator = np.zeros((len(rhos), len(thetas)), dtype=np.uint8)\n",
    "    yis, xis = np.nonzero(img)\n",
    "\n",
    "    for idx in range(len(xis)):\n",
    "        x = xis[idx]\n",
    "        y = yis[idx]\n",
    "        temp_rhos = x * np.cos(np.deg2rad(thetas)) + y * np.sin(np.deg2rad(thetas))\n",
    "        temp_rhos = temp_rhos / rho_res + rho_max\n",
    "        m, n = accumulator.shape\n",
    "        valid_idxs = np.nonzero((temp_rhos < m) & (thetas < n))\n",
    "        temp_rhos = temp_rhos[valid_idxs]\n",
    "        temp_thetas = thetas[valid_idxs]\n",
    "        c = np.stack([temp_rhos,temp_thetas], 1)\n",
    "        cc = np.ascontiguousarray(c).view(np.dtype((np.void, c.dtype.itemsize * c.shape[1])))\n",
    "        _,idxs,counts = np.unique(cc, return_index=True, return_counts=True)\n",
    "        uc = c[idxs].astype(np.uint)\n",
    "        accumulator[uc[:,0], uc[:,1]] += counts.astype(np.uint)\n",
    "    accumulator = cv2.normalize(accumulator, accumulator, 0, 255,\n",
    "                                cv2.NORM_MINMAX, dtype=cv2.CV_8UC1)\n",
    "    return accumulator, thetas, rhos"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def lines_draw(img, peaks, rhos, thetas):\n",
    "    lines = []\n",
    "    for peak in peaks:\n",
    "        rho = rhos[peak[0]]\n",
    "        theta = thetas[peak[1]] * np.pi / 180.0\n",
    "        a = np.cos(theta); b = np.sin(theta)\n",
    "        pt0 = rho * np.array([a,b])\n",
    "        pt1 = tuple((pt0 + 1000 * np.array([-b,a])).astype(int))\n",
    "        pt2 = tuple((pt0 - 1000 * np.array([-b,a])).astype(int))\n",
    "        cv2.line(img, pt1, pt2, (255,0,0), 2)\n",
    "        lines.append([pt1,pt2])\n",
    "    return img,lines"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def findIntersection(x1,y1,x2,y2,x3,y3,x4,y4):\n",
    "    px= ( (x1*y2-y1*x2)*(x3-x4)-(x1-x2)*(x3*y4-y3*x4) ) / ( (x1-x2)*(y3-y4)-(y1-y2)*(x3-x4) ) \n",
    "    py= ( (x1*y2-y1*x2)*(y3-y4)-(y1-y2)*(x3*y4-y3*x4) ) / ( (x1-x2)*(y3-y4)-(y1-y2)*(x3-x4) )\n",
    "    return [px, py]"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "for name in files:\n",
    "    print(path + \"\\\\\" + name)\n",
    "    img = plt.imread(path + \"\\\\\" + name)\n",
    "    res = img.copy()\n",
    "    plt.imshow(img)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    width, height = img.shape[:2]\n",
    "    print(img.shape)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    gray = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n",
    "    plt.imshow(gray, cmap='gray')\n",
    "    plt.show()   \n",
    "    \n",
    "    blurred = cv2.GaussianBlur(gray, (3, 3), 0)\n",
    "    plt.imshow(blurred, cmap='gray')\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \n",
    "    cann = cv2.Canny(blurred, 0, 255)\n",
    "    plt.imshow(cann, cmap='gray')\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    H, thetas, rhos = hough_lines(cann)\n",
    "    plt.imshow(H, cmap='gray')\n",
    "    plt.show() \n",
    "    \n",
    "    peaks = hough_peaks(H, nps=15, e=100, size=50)\n",
    "    H_peaks = H.copy()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for peak in peaks:\n",
    "        cv2.circle(H_peaks, tuple(peak[::-1]), 5, (255,255,255), -1)\n",
    "    plt.imshow(H_peaks, cmap='gray')\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    lines,pts = lines_draw(img, peaks, rhos, thetas)\n",
    "    plt.imshow(lines)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "    intersectionPts = []\n",
    "    print(pts)\n",
    "    for i  in range(len(pts)-1):\n",
    "        for j in range(i,len(pts)):\n",
    "            x,y = findIntersection(pts[i][0][0] ,\n",
    "                                   pts[i][0][1] ,\n",
    "                                   pts[i][1][0] ,\n",
    "                                   pts[i][1][1] ,\n",
    "                                   pts[j][0][0] ,\n",
    "                                   pts[j][0][1] ,\n",
    "                                   pts[j][1][0] ,\n",
    "                                   pts[j][1][1] )\n",
    "            if (np.isfinite(x) and x < height and x > 0 and\n",
    "                np.isfinite(y) and y < width and y > 0):\n",
    "                    intersectionPts.append((int(x),int(y)))\n",
    "                    cv2.circle(lines,(int(x),int(y)), 5, (0,255,0), -1)\n",
    "                 \n",
    "    plt.imshow(lines)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    \n",
    "\n",
    "    \n",
    "    struct1 = OrderedDict()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \n",
    "    used = []\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for x,y in intersectionPts:\n",
    "        if x not in struct1.keys():\n",
    "            struct1[x] = list()\n",
    "        struct1[x] = sorted(struct1[x] + [y])\n",
    "\n",
    "        \n",
    "    for k,v in struct1.items():       \n",
    "        print(k,v)\n",
    "        for i in range(len(v)-1):\n",
    "            y1 = v[i]\n",
    "            y2 = v[i+1]\n",
    "            \n",
    "            \n",
    "            for k2,v2 in struct1.items():\n",
    "                if(k != k2):\n",
    "                    if y1 in v2 and y2 in v2 and (k,y1) not in used and (k2,y2) not in used:\n",
    "                        used.append((k,y1))\n",
    "                        used.append((k2,y2))\n",
    "                        print(k,y1,k2,y2)\n",
    "                        minx = min(k,k2)\n",
    "                        maxx = max(k,k2)\n",
    "                        miny = min(y1,y2)\n",
    "                        maxy = max(y1,y2)\n",
    "                        cv2.rectangle(res, (minx,miny) , (maxx,maxy), (0,0,255), 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.imshow(res)\n",
    "    plt.show() \n",
    "    \n",
    "\n",
    "    \n"
   ]
